ount for redrive policies.\n/// Messages that exceed this receive count are moved to the DLQ.\nconst DEFAULT_MAX_RECEIVE_COUNT: u32 = 10;\n```\n\nReplace the hardcoded `3` in `declare_sqs_unsequenced` and `declare_sqs_sequenced` with `DEFAULT_MAX_RECEIVE_COUNT`.\n\n### Fix 4: Fix double get_retry_count call in extract_dead_metadata\n\n**File:** `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`\n\nChange `extract_dead_metadata` to reuse the metadata's retry_count:\n\n```rust\nfn extract_dead_metadata(\n    msg: &aws_sdk_sqs::types::Message,\n    queue_name: &str,\n) -> DeadMessageMetadata {\n    let metadata = extract_metadata(msg);\n    let death_count = metadata.retry_count;\n    DeadMessageMetadata {\n        message: metadata,\n        reason: Some(\"max_receives_exceeded\".into()),\n        original_queue: Some(queue_name.to_string()),\n        death_count,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Fix 5: Request only needed SQS system attributes instead of All\n\n**File:** `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`\n\nIn `consume_loop_concurrent`, change:\n```rust\n.message_system_attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::All)\n```\nto:\n```rust\n.message_system_attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount)\n```\n\nIn `consume_loop_sequenced`, change `All` to request both needed attributes:\n```rust\n.message_system_attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount)\n.message_system_attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::MessageGroupId)\n```\n\nIn the DLQ loop (`consume_dlq_loop`), change to just:\n```rust\n.message_system_attribute_names(aws_sdk_sqs::types::MessageSystemAttributeName::ApproximateReceiveCount)\n```\n\n### Fix 6: Extract shared handler timeout logic\n\n**File:** `src/backends/sns/consumer.rs`\n\nAdd a shared helper:\n```rust\nasync fn invoke_handler<T: Topic, H: MessageHandler<T>>(\n    handler: &H,\n    message: T::Message,\n    metadata: MessageMetadata,\n    timeout: