            "content": "# Shove v0.4 — API & Architecture Refactor\n\n## Goal\n\nSimplify the public API, consolidate internal deserialization paths, and break up the largest module — while preserving the existing sequenced/unsequenced split and Outcome semantics.\n\nBreaking changes are acceptable.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Consolidate deserialization — delete `typed.rs`\n\n### Problem\n\nTwo deserialization paths exist: `consumer.rs` does inline JSON deserialization and metadata extraction, and `typed.rs` provides `TypedAdapter`/`DlqAdapter` behind a `RawHandler` trait that does the same thing.\n\n### Change\n\n- Delete `src/backends/rabbitmq/typed.rs` entirely.\n- Delete the `RawHandler` trait.\n- Move the pure helper functions into a new `src/backends/rabbitmq/headers.rs`:\n  - `get_retry_count(delivery) -> u32`\n  - `extract_message_metadata(delivery) -> MessageMetadata`\n  - `extract_string_headers(delivery) -> HashMap<String, String>`\n  - `extract_dead_metadata(delivery) -> DeadMessageMetadata`\n- The consumer calls these helpers directly and works with `MessageHandler<T>` everywhere — no adapter layer.\n\n### Files\n\n- **Added:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/headers.rs`\n- **Deleted:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/typed.rs`\n- **Modified:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/consumer.rs`, `src/backends/rabbitmq/mod.rs`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Split `consumer.rs` — extract routing into `router.rs`\n\n### Problem\n\n`consumer.rs` is ~580 lines handling the consume loop, outcome routing, header manipulation, and reconnection logic.\n\n### Change\n\nExtract outcome routing into `src/backends/rabbitmq/router.rs`:\n\n- `route_retry(channel, delivery, topology, retry_count)` — publishes to the appropriate hold queue based on retry count, acks the original delivery.\n- `route_defer(channel, delivery, topology)` — if hold queues exist, publishes to hold[0] without incrementing the retry counter, acks. If no hold queues exist, nacks with requeue=true (message returns to the back of the queue).\n- `route_reject(channel, delivery)` — nacks without requeue; broker routes to DLQ.\n- `route_ack(channel, delivery)` — simple ack.\n\n`consumer.rs` retains: `consume_loop`, `consume_loop_sequenced`, `run`, `run_sequenced`, `run_dlq`, handler invocation with timeout, reconnection logic. It delegates outcome handling to `router.rs` and metadata extraction to `headers.rs`.\n\nExpected result: `consumer.rs` drops from ~580 to ~350 lines. Routing logic becomes independently testable.\n\n### Defer fallback behavior\n\nWhen a handler returns `Defer` but the topology has no hold queues, `route_defer` falls back to nack with requeue=true. The message returns to the queue without delay. Hold queues give users control over the delay, but `Defer` works regardless of topology configuration.\n\n### Files\n\n- **Added:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/router.rs`\n- **Modified:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/consumer.rs`, `src/backends/rabbitmq/mod.rs`\n\n---\n\n## 3. Registry auto-declares topology\n\n### Problem\n\nUsers must manually create a channel, call `RabbitMqTopologyDeclarer.declare::<T>(&channel)` for each topic, then separately register consumer groups. Easy to forget a step.\n\n### Change\n\n`ConsumerGroupRegistry::register()` becomes async and declares topology internally before registering the group. The registry already holds a `RabbitMqClient`, so it creates a channel and declares via `RabbitMqTopologyDeclarer`.\n\n```rust\n// Before (3 steps)\nlet channel = client.create_channel().await?;\nRabbitMqTopologyDeclarer.declare::<MyTopic>(&channel).await?;\nregistry.register::<MyTopic, _>(handler, config);\n\n// After (1 step)\nregistry.register::<MyTopic, _>(handler, config).await?;\n```\n\n`TopologyDeclarer` trait and `RabbitMqTopologyDeclarer` remain public for standalone use (e.g. publisher-only services that need to declare topology without running consumers).\n\n### API break\n\n`register()` signature changes from sync to `async fn register(...) -> Result<()>`.\n\n### Files\n\n- **Modified:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/registry.rs`\n\n---\n\n## 4. API ergonomics cleanup\n\n### 4a. `ConsumerGroupConfig` takes `RangeInclusive`\n\n```rust\n// Before\nConsumerGroupConfig::new(1, 5)\n\n// After\nConsumerGroupConfig::new(1..=5)\n```\n\nClearer intent, impossible to swap min/max. The constructor takes `RangeInclusive<u16>`.\n\n### 4b. Internalize `ManagementClient`\n\n```rust\n// Before\nlet mgmt = ManagementClient::new(mgmt_config);\nlet autoscaler = Autoscaler::new(mgmt, AutoscalerConfig::default());\n\n// After\nlet autoscaler = Autoscaler::new(&mgmt_config, AutoscalerConfig::default());\n```\n\n`Autoscaler::new` creates the `ManagementClient` internally. `ManagementClient` is no longer re-exported from `pub mod rabbitmq`. The `QueueStatsProvider` trait remains public for testing and custom implementations.\n\n### 4c. Type alias\n\n```rust\n// In error.rs\npub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, ShoveError>;\n```\n\nUsed throughout the crate to replace `Result<T, ShoveError>`.\n\n### Files\n\n- **Modified:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/consumer_group.rs` (4a)\n- **Modified:** `src/backends/rabbitmq/autoscaler.rs`, `src/backends/rabbitmq/management.rs` (4b)\n- **Modified:** `src/error.rs`, `src/lib.rs`, and all files returning `Result<_, ShoveError>` (4c)\n\n---\n\n## 5. Audit recursion guard\n\n### Problem\n\n`ShoveAuditHandler` publishes audit records to `shove-audit-log`. If a consumer for the audit topic is itself wrapped in `Audited`, it creates an infinite publish loop.\n\n### Change\n\n`Audited::handle()` checks if the current topic's queue name matches the audit log topic's queue name. If so, it skips auditing and delegates directly to the inner handler.\n\n```rust\nlet is_audit_topic = T::topology().queue() == AuditLog::topology().queue();\nif is_audit_topic {\n    return self.inner.handle(message, metadata).await;\n}\n```\n\nRuntime cost: one string comparison per message.\n\n### Files\n\n- **Modified:** `src/audit.rs`\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Outcome enum changes (keep Ack/Retry/Reject/Defer as-is)\n- Unifying sequenced/unsequenced consumer paths (keep separate)\n- Spawner type alias rework\n- Handler panic handling\n- Derive macro for Topic\n- App-level builder (ShoveApp)\n\n---\n\n## Summary of public API breaks\n\n| Item | Before | After |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| `registry.register()` | sync, no topology | async, auto-declares topology |\n| `ConsumerGroupConfig::new()` | `(min, max)` | `(min..=max)` |\n| `Autoscaler::new()` | `(impl QueueStatsProvider, config)` | `(&ManagementConfig, config)` |\n| `ManagementClient` | re-exported | private (use `QueueStatsProvider` trait for custom impls) |\n| `RawHandler` | public trait | deleted |\n| `TypedAdapter` / `DlqAdapter` | public structs | deleted |\n\n## New internal modules\n\n| Module | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `src/backends/rabbitmq/headers.rs` | AMQP header parsing helpers |\n| `src/backends/rabbitmq/router.rs` | Outcome-based message routing |\n",
